# Sportstensor Week 3 Update
@sportstensor・41 

- Distribution curve shaping up, those who are making more accurate predictions are earning more incentive
- Added snapshot function to collect historical miner prediction data
- We hired an fe dev to work on the Sportstensor Dashboard v1.1 to include snapshot data
- Our ml engineer working on the NFL model and the rest of our team sourcing high-quality data
- Rolling out **a European league** model for match outcome predictions on 16th 🤫
- Begun outreach to companies, networks and other subnets for partnership and collaboration 👀 
- Published a medium article to help you better understand what Sportstensor is about: https://medium.com/@sportstensor/revolutionizing-sports-analytics-through-decentralized-intelligence-5b8536eb6687

## 🤼 Individual Player Predictions

A *huge* task that is currently under way is moving to our next phase of predictions. We are only 3 weeks old but we do not rest on our laurels if we are to pioneer decentralized sports analytics. Match outcome predictions are stable and thriving, it's time to tackle individual player predictions. The complexity involved with this undertaking **cannot be understated** as you can imagine how many players per team in any given sport/league and the kinds of analytics to derive such as runs, batted runs, hits, strikeouts etc. **Mind-boggling.**

As the first to do something like this we know it wont be easy, but if it was - it wouldn't be worth building. Despite the daunting journey ahead, the team are ecstatic about the possibilities.

Todo (condensed and summarized):
- Begin integration plans for Individual Player Predictions (IPP) in to current validator <> miner flow
- Generate a list of players, define tier 1 stats, generate prediction combinations, secure data flow
- Implement in to web app for users to request IPP
- Ground truth remains as player results after the match
- Research for benchmarking with public studies

Don't forget you can check out our dashboard v1 here: https://dashboard.sportstensor.com/
